Ad Text:
As a Senior MRI Analyst, you will play a pivotal role in supporting the organisation's commercial real estate operations by leveraging MRI Software and its associated applications to deliver actionable insights, streamline reporting, and enhance system capabilities. You will act as a subject matter expert on MRI modules, lead system enhancements, and collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive data-driven decision-making.

The tasks and responsibilities for the role include:

Management oversight, training and mentoring of the Systems Support team, 2 x Manila staff
MRI ERP system data updates using SQL
Management Studio query and integrity checks
Deep dive in system back-end queries · Reporting modifications and cabinet file progression
Discussions with external consultants/MRI
2nd level Jira issue review/triage
System error investigation, solution and root cause analysis
Bank account setup / Cash Mapping
Data Migration support and tasks · Data extraction to support Power Bi reports/SQL server integration
Internal Business Owner client reporting/data extracts
Investment Modelling support set up
Budget and Reforecast training and support
Treasury Management system approvals & admin support
Scoping of new items for automation and system improvement, including business requirements for small projects
Monthly Reporting to the GM
Periodic audit investigation and reporting
Training on utilisation of SQL (MRI query) for staff

Aptitude:

Positive can-do attitude
Team player, Leads by Example
Openness to help the wider business
Embraces change and sees new systems as a chance to grow in the role
Strong attention to detail
Strong Communicator and an Influencer
Strong controls and governance focus
Continuous Improvement Focus
Ability to communicate clearly in both email and phone discussion
Working knowledge of Excel and Word

Essential

MRI - Support and Triage experience / exposure and related systems like Jira is essential
Experience in leading a team is essential
Understanding of Accounting principles and knowledge is essential Not Essential
Property industry experience preferable, not essential

Experience with the following would be beneficial:

MyBuildings, Sage, or other larger ERP systems - Exposure to Treasury or Loan Management systems.

Job Type: Contract (6 months likely extension)

Salary: 750 per day

We are seeking an experienced Data Solution Designer to lead our modern data platform, manage high-performing teams, and drive end-to-end delivery of enterprise analytics solutions. You will define strategy, implement scalable cloud-native data platforms, and partner with business & product teams to enable data-driven decision making.

Key Responsibilities

Define and deliver the enterprise Data & Analytics strategy, quarterly roadmaps, and long-term platform vision.
Lead and mentor Analytics Engineers, Data Engineers, BI Developers and Analysts.
Partner with Product, Marketing, Finance, and Tech teams to align data priorities.
Drive governance, data quality, security, platform lifecycle management and FinOps optimisation.
Own architecture & operations of Snowflake/GCP/AWS analytics platforms.
Oversee ingestion pipelines, ELT/ETL development, modelling and analytics layer design.
Implement DataOps, MLOps and Infrastructure-as-Code practices (Terraform).
Ensure reliability, scalability, cost-efficiency of the full data stack.

Key Skills & Experience

Snowflake, BigQuery or AWS data platforms
dbt (Core/Cloud), Fivetran, Segment
Data Lake architecture (S3/GCS/ADLS)
Streaming (Kafka, Pub/Sub)
Terraform / IaC / GitOps
Data modelling (star, vault, semantic models)
Looker, Tableau or equivalent
Experience enabling Data Science teams (Feature Stores, ML pipelines)
